Description: Papyrus written with black ink with demotic legal text on recto (23 ll.), verso pasted down. Thompson's MS Catalogue: "Cession of one-third of a share of land by Har(?)-poeris son of Nechutes to Petearsemtheus son of Panobchunis. Scribe Harsiese / Nebktum son of Sebekhotep? Date. year 19 Thoth 29 of Ptol. Alexander = BC. 96 Oct. 14 [...] cf. no.10491. NB. no. 10495 seems to be draft for this document. They are both in the same handwriting".
Curator's comments: Cf. entry in www.trismegistos.org - DAHT. Bibliography Felber, H., Demotische Ackerpachtverträge (ÄA 58). Wiesbaden, 1997, pg 59. Edited in S.E. Thomas Cambridge PhD diss. Text 25 in Shore's Manuscript Catalogue of Demotic Gebelein Papyri in the British Museum. Publication in progress (S.E. Thomas).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (332) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/332)
